      "rationale": "A three-level mesh convergence study was performed on the pedicle screw shank and rod interface regions. Grid Convergence Index (GCI) was 1.8%, 2.3%, and 1.5% for stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm, respectively, all below the 5% threshold. Gradation 3 achieved, exceeding required Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual norms below 1e-6 for all load steps; energy balance error < 0.1%.",
      "rationale": "Newton-Raphson residual norms converged to below 1e-6 for all 42 load increments across the three QoI evaluations. Energy balance error was 0.04%. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of model setup by a second analyst; documented pre-analysis plan specifying boundary conditions, material assignments, and contact definitions prior to simulation execution.",
      "rationale": "A pre-analysis plan was documented and signed before simulation runs. An independent analyst reviewed boundary conditions, contact pair definitions, and material property assignments. No discrepancies were identified. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Nonlinear elastic-plastic material model with isotropic hardening; frictional contact at screw-rod interface; geometric nonlinearity enabled for large-displacement regime.",
      "rationale": "The FEA model employs a bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity model calibrated from Ti-6Al-4V tensile coupon data. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) at the screw-rod interface was validated against torque-angle data. Geometric nonlinearity (NLGEOM ON) captures the large-displacement response observed experimentally at 40 mm. Model form is consistent with the physics of the compression-bending test. Gradation 3 achieved and required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from lot-specific tensile coupon testing of the same material lot as test constructs; geometric dimensions from CMM measurements of production screws and rods.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (114 GPa), yield strength (880 MPa), and tangent modulus (1.2 GPa) were measured from five tensile coupons machined from the same Ti-6Al-4V rod stock. Screw and rod geometry was digitized via CMM with ±5 µm accuracy. Input uncertainty was propagated using Monte Carlo sampling (n=1000). Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 production-representative constructs from at least two independent lots; constructs assembled per IFU by trained operators.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs were assembled from two production lots of 7.5 mm non-cannulated pedicle screws and titanium rods, following the IFU torque specifications. Constructs were distributed across two independent laboratories to assess inter-laboratory variability. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span at least two clinically relevant load levels or construct configurations; environmental conditions (temperature, humidity) controlled and documented.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted at a single load configuration (ASTM F1717 standard setup, 5 mm/min crosshead speed, ambient temperature 23±2°C). While environmental conditions were controlled and documented, only one load condition was evaluated. This limits generalizability to other loading scenarios but is consistent with the COU scope. Gradation 2 achieved; required Gradation 3. This gap is acknowledged and accepted given the regulatory precedent for single-condition F1717 testing.",
      "hasWeakener": []
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model input parameters (geometry, material, assembly torque) demonstrably equivalent to those of the physical test constructs within stated uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "CMM-measured screw and rod dimensions were used directly in the CAD-to-mesh pipeline. Lot-specific material properties from tensile coupons were assigned. Assembly torque was matched to the IFU specification applied during construct assembly. Equivalency verified by overlay of CAD geometry with CT scan of one representative construct (mean surface deviation 0.03 mm). Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
