      "rationale": "All three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and absolute percent difference < 10%. The comparison framework follows the approach described in the validation literature cited in the wasDerivedFrom reference, with validation uncertainty uval computed from experimental variability (N=11) and model input uncertainty (Monte Carlo). Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) are directly linked to the clinical failure modes (fatigue fracture, permanent deformation) and are the QoIs specified in the regulatory submission.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness correlates with load sharing between the implant and the spine; yield force and force at 40 mm displacement are the primary ASTM F1717 acceptance metrics used in 510(k) submissions for pedicle screw systems. All three QoIs are directly relevant to the COU decision. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
